^c@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Based on the bidding, if you determine that the partnership's combined point count is 33 or more, you know that you are in the slam range. However, 33 points by itself is not sufficient to bid slam.|
PG| ***** 20 ***** |


AT|

Upon opening carefully listen to partner's response and count the total value of the partnership before further bidding. As opener, your hand falls into one of 3 ranges:|
PG| ***** 21 ***** |


AT|

- a minimum opening hand, is |CP|8|AT|13-16 Declarer Points|
pg| ***** 22 ***** |


CP||AT|
- a medium opening hand is |CP|8|AT|17-19 Declarer Points|
pg| ***** 23 ***** |


CP||AT|
- a maximum opening hand is |CP|8|AT|20+ Declarer Points|
pg| ***** 24 ***** |


CP||AT|

As responder, your hand falls into one of 3 ranges:|
PG| ***** 25 ***** |


AT|

- a minimum response is |CP|8|AT|6-9 Dummy Points|
pg| ***** 26 ***** |


CP||AT|
- an invitational response (such as a limit raise) is |CP|8|AT|10-12 Dummy Points|
pg| ***** 27 ***** |


CP||AT|
- a maximum response is |CP|8|AT|13+ Dummy Points.|
pg| ***** 28 ***** |


CP||AT|

With a maximum response, you must force to game. Note that until you find a fit, you use Starting Points to evaluate your hand. Once you find a fit, you use the Declarer and Dummy addon points. Therefore, your hand can increase in value (and hence change which range it belongs to) once a fit is established. |
PG| ***** 29 ***** |


