{            Control Bids            }
^-|HT|d|CP|8|AT|^c@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Game Force Response, "GF" means, if partner opens, and you have 13-16 Dummy Points, you know you should at least be in game. On the other hand, If both partners have medium hands, you are in the slam range since 17 + 17 = 34, And, if partner opens (which shows at least 13 Starting Points), and you have 20+ Dummy Points, you are in slam range, since 20 + 13 = 33. |
PG| ***** 30 ***** |


CP||AT|
^-
{ HAVING 33 POINTS IS A "NECESSARY BUT NOT SUFFICIENT CONDITION" FOR SLAM }
^-|
PG| ***** 31 ***** |


CP||AT|

The other thing you have to make sure is that you do not have 2 losers off the top.  We all know some form of Blackwood, which allows us to check to make sure we are not missing two Aces. Obviously, if we are missing two Aces (assuming no voids) we cannot bid slam, even if the combined hands have 33 points or more. However, we might only be missing one Ace and still not make slam. That is because we might be missing both the A and K in one particular suit, and neither partner has a singleton.|
PG| ***** 32 ***** |


AT|

So, in order to bid slam, we have to make sure we have "|CP|8|at|control|cp||at|" in every suit. We can either have |CP|8|FP|2|at|FIRST ROUND CONTROL|cp||FP||at| or |CP|8|FP|2|at|SECOND ROUND CONTROL|cp||at|.|
PG| ***** 33 ***** |


CP|8|AT|

FIRST ROUND CONTROL |CP||FP||AT|means we can take the first trick when a suit is played. That means we either have the |CP|8|FP|2|at|ACE|cp||FP||at| or a |CP|8|FP|2|at|VOID|cp||FP||at| in the suit.|
PG| ***** 34 ***** |


CP|8|FP|2|AT|

SECOND ROUND CONTROL |CP||FP||AT|means we have the |FP|2|AT|KING|FP||AT| or a |FP|2|AT|SINGLETON|FP||AT| and that the opponents cannot take the |FP|2|AT|FIRST TWO TRICKS|FP||AT|. They may take the first trick, but we can take the second trick.|
PG| ***** 35 ***** |


