^B@2^Y@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||fp||at|You can bid 4@D, which by implication shows a spade control. The reason it shows a spade control is because partner denied a spade control when he bid 4@C.  So, if you do not have a spade control, you know that you have 2 spade losers, and therefore must stop at 4@H. The point of control bids is to determine that you at least have second round control in all suits. If you know for sure that you lack second round control in a suit, then you should stop in game right away.  If partner explicitly skips a suit when making a control bid, that denies a control in that suit. If you also lack a control in that suit, you know you cannot be in slam.

